Policy 18.1 - Integrity Controls (Addressable) - discusses using secure methods that protect ePHI during transmission. For example, the use of Secure Sockets Layer (SSL) when transmitting ePHI via an Internet Browser. Policy 18.2 - Encryption (Addressable) - discusses using encryption to protect ePHI.
